# AI tooling feedback loop

The agent tooling in this repo (`w check --json`, `bin/wtest`, the
edit-check hook, `bin/wmcp`, `bin/wlsp`, the skills in `.cursor/skills/`)
is dogfooded: the agents that use it are expected to maintain its backlog.

- If you hit friction, a bug, a missing capability, or have an
  improvement idea while using any of these tools, add a short entry
  (symptom, where observed, suggested direction) to
  `docs/projects/ai_tooling_next_steps.md` in the same PR — unless it is
  already listed there.
- When you implement one of its items, delete the entry and record the
  summary in the status section of `docs/projects/ai_tooling.md` instead.
- Do not let the file grow stale entries: if an item turns out to be
  wrong or obsolete, remove it and say why in the commit message.
